The stars & planets impact us SO MUCH. They are always working behind the scenes to help us become a truer version of yourself. Venus came out of the underworld today - have you felt extra heavy and down the past few weeks (and especially the last few days 🥴) only to wake up feeling unexplainably better today? It’s Venus.

Some Qs to ask yourself.

1. What layers have you been shedding since January that has helped you reveal the truth of who you are?

2. What has been the biggest challenge for you over the past couple weeks?

3. Who are you emerging as today? What new perspective do you have on who you are and your life? - Answer this one below!

4. What are you going to do differently going forward?

@tamibrunk and I lead “Written in the Stars” today to help the women in the Star understand that you are selves better through shamanic astrology and it was so incredible to all be together on this Venus Rising day.

Xox

Sarah

It’s been a BIG week. We moved out of our house for a year to a year and a half to build our dream home, and although we are extremely excited, adjusting to a significantly smaller space has been a thing.

In human design my primary sense is outer vision - meaning, my sight - so what things looks like is very important to me. It impacts my mood a lot. 

So, when I came to living in a rental for a while, I knew I needed to make it beautiful.

I put up temp wallpaper and painted before we moved in, and everything else is stuff from our home.

A year is a long time, and I sense there are a lot of changes for all us coming in 2023, and I knew I needed my nest to hold me.

Which little scene is your fave!? It was so fun for me to stretch my design muscles. Can’t wait to use them on our dream home.

If you have a man in your life who is on the inner work path or wants to start, I want to make sure they know about the amazing work @jonathanbrajtbord is doing. Jonathan is a Urologist, Dad and college football player who loves working on himself, is spiritual and is standing for a new paradigm of masculine power.

In my experience a lot of men’s coaching is very theory based, and Jonathan‘s way is incredibly practical. He connects inner work to how men deliberately change how they show up in their marriages, with their kids and in their careers.

For the past year Jonathan has been leading large groups of men through his 6-week online program, Men’s Work and he just announced a Men’s Retreat at Hawthorn Farm (our home & retreat center), Fortitude in February.  Think deep transformation, connection with other men and physical challenge IN THE SNOW.

If you have a man in your life who is looking to change the way he sees himself and the world, please send him the info.

Many of my clients husbands have been working with Jonathan this year and I have heard from them first hand but how much their lives have changed now that their husbands are doing inner work.

@jonathanbrajtbord is going live to talk about his fortitude retreat tonight at 8:30 Eastern. It would be a great way for the men in your life to get to know Jonathan.

Here’s to the whole family getting the support they need ❤️.

Happy Full Moon in Gemini! In this video I talk about my journey from being a negative, grumpy sourpuss to having my life centered around play & joy - AND the radical impact that had on my company and on my money.

I also announced that I am opening up enrollment for The Star for today only, so if you want to take a radical leap into your Soul’s Work and are ready to move mountains for yourself to be there tomorrow (you will also get the recording) send me a DM 🔥.

Happy Full Moon Witches!!

Xox

Sarah

To all the women who came together for The Star, thank you for bringing your full heart, a lot of courage and your trust in me. Wow. What.a.day.

When things feel hard on the surface, it usually means there is a lot happening energetically underneath the surface.

Even though I was focused on packing & moving & trying not to lose my sh*t, what was really happening was I was revisiting old wounds and traumas from the past five years. And it was HEAVY.

Some of it came in the form of old clothes, broken furniture, things left behind from other people and some came from @jonathanbrajtbord and I enacting old patterns so I could clearly see that THIS DOESN’T WORK ANYMORE. The Goddess will put things in our path over and over until we’ve truly learned the lesson 😒.

Instead of being fixated on what “happened” we chose to focus on what we were being asked to learn.

On Thursday, @jonathanbrajtbord and I went to our empty house, named out loud to each other all of the  patterns we want to release and named all of the wounds and hard stuff that had happened. Then we had one last dance in the living room. The junk guy hauled away all of our stuff that doesn’t support the people we are becoming this morning, and I truly feel complete.

I’m excited for our next chapter.

“I don’t know what you did, Sarah, but you’re on fire.” 👈🏼 I’ve heard this so many times this year.

Here’s my big secret: I started doing what I loved.

I stopped asking
“What can I do to make more money?”
“What would feel easy?”
“How can I stand out?”

And I simply asked myself:
“What would be so freaking fun?”
“How can I express myself completely?”
“What is the most true thing I can create?”

We have been brainwashed to believe that will be less successful if we actually just do what we want. 

First of all, the most important measure of success is our happiness and well being. And I couldn’t be measuring higher. AND my impact has dramatically increased, and my financial abundance has increased. Your life gets to be a win win - because I know so many of us here are financially responsible for others, whether it’s our children, partners, parents or employees, so money we make matters.

You don’t have to trade your soul for success. 

Today, ask yourself:
“If I could do anything and guarantee I would make the exact amount of money I wanted, what would I do?”

And then the work comes in cultivating the courage to do it, and that is developed through your sacred practice and your relationship to the divine.

Want to share below what you would do? I’d love to hear.

If you want to be a highly valued, highly respected, highly paid Sacred Woman in your industry - whether that’s medicine, publishing, higher education, coaching, HR, law or lifestyle products - then I’d love to talk to you about the Winter Council.

The Winter Council is for the woman who is ready to bring her sacred abilities and true self to her big work in the world, while reaching levels of success and impact she’s never experienced before. She is probably the first in her family, friend group and industry to stand as a Sacred Woman and call in next level success, so she desires a group of woman who are doing the same to hold her as she steps over this threshold. 

The Winter Council runs from January 15th -  April 15th and includes a retreat to Tulum, Mexico (!!!) and multiple online gatherings for hot-seats and group coaching (all the dates are on the application page). This is our third Council gathering and the women who have come before you have experienced life changing transformation in their lives and in their work.

I started the Council because I believe that Sacred Women should be as respected and highly paid as Doctors, Lawyers and Bankers because the level of depth, transformation, innovation and holding we bring when we bring our sacred skills is a necessity as our world evolves. 

I want sacred women in all of the positions of power, but that can’t happen if we are hiding our sacred abilities, or downplaying the importance of them.

As a women who went to the #1 liberal arts college in the country and was slated to become successful in a traditional career, it was radical for me to quit my marketing job to be an emotional eating coach. 13 years later I am now an ordained Priestess and have built a multi 7-figure spiritual lifestyle company that supports tens of thousands of people in 43 countries.

If you know you’re meant to be in this incredible group, you can apply via the link in my bio.

The cosmos is always trying to get us in alignment with our best selves, and the Winter Solstice is all about space and stillness. We are in the darkest days of the year, and we are being invited (maybe a little too aggressively?) to take the medicine.

What’s been coming up for you in the mystery school of your life right now?

I used to think that creating more success in my company meant better strategies or working harder.

Turns out that my external results were a direct reflection of my internal state, my health, my relationships and how much fun I was having.

I wanted to experience radical expansion of my mission in the world, so I had to enact radical change in my personal life.

Daily cold plunges in my lake are one of the biggest and best changes I made for my physical and mental health. I can now stay in for 4 minutes 💪🏼.

This year I also
- Prioritized an hour #sacredstart every morning
- Created friendships that inspire me and celebrate my bigness. 
- Got Ordained in my spiritual lineage, a decision I made for my own spiritual growth.
- Did a massive toxin & parasite detox.
- Travelled to places I was putting off.
- Consciously created more fun and sacred moments with my 3 kids.
- Went on a weekly date nights with my husband and took 3 solo trips.

What in your personal life isn’t up to your standard of excellence? Where do you want to make radical changes?

If you are a leader in your industry, corporation or company who wants to bring more sacred work, meaning and soul into your work and role, it would be honor to have you apply for The Council.

Hanukkah hits different this year. With all of the hate circulating, I have become such a fierce stand for this faith, this lineage, this great people. I grew up Christian and am a Priestess of the Sacred Feminine, and I did not convert to Judaism - AND that has nothing to do with my efforts in nurturing and preserving the faith and culture in our home.

The biggest thing I heard from people when we decided to raise our kids in multiple faiths was that Judaism would get lost inside of the fanfare of Christmas and Christianity - all I can say is that is entirely up to the parents and the way they raise their children.

We have consciously created a household where we make space for all of our beliefs and lineages, and we hold that they are not in competition, and one does not exclude the other. We have found that not only do our multiple faiths and belief systems coexist, but they actually amplify each other when we look for the similarities.

Our homes need to be a microcosm of the world we want to create. Our traditions shape who we become. Take some time today to think about the messages you want your kids to receive during this holiday time. How can your traditions communicate your values?

Happy Hanukkah!!

Our family is a Sacred system. And that is so hard and exhausting when one of your kids is having a hard time.  We all have those moments where we just throw up or hands and feel like it’s too much. I’ve been feeling pretty overwhelmed and hopeless these days, and I knew I had to dig deep.

When I looked at our family system with a sacred lens, I remember that whatever hard emotional or health situation is going on isn’t taking away from our lives but it’s actually redirecting our lives towards an even bigger and brighter future. It is a redirect, a re-organization.

It is also super important to bring in other forms of support like therapy and physical health support, and I believe that adding in the Sacred is an important piece that a lot of us miss in parenting.

If any of you are having a hard time out there, I see you, I love you, we got this.

Share this message with someone who needs to hear it today.

Love,

Sarah

This is a letter to the women who have a hard time pausing…

Hi! I’m Sarah, and I am a over doer.

The majority of this comes from an insane amount of enthusiasm for life, and there are times when I have a resistance to pausing because I have a deep seeded belief that my worth is based on my productivity or somehow I will “miss the boat”.

Knowing this is part of the way patriarchy has brainwashed women to be constantly productive in order to prove our worth, has helped me separate this from my identity.

Earlier this week I was experiencing a lot of frustration and overwhelm which is a sign that it was time for me to pause. It was not an easy decision to make as I had a lot of things on my plate that felt urgent and important, but I am learning that when my body talks to me I have to listen.

This morning, my youngest woke up with a high fever and then my middle threw up at school in the afternoon so I had to pick her up early. I canceled my whole day, off loaded the rest of the shopping onto @jonathanbrajtbord and just got in touch with what was most important during the solstice portal, and that is sitting down and doing very little.

Often times during this time of year doing the bare minimum is where the magic lies.

One thing that is helping me pause is putting times on my calendar when I can get back to big dreaming and planning of 2023. I know that there’s so much potential for a really epic beautiful year for all of us, and know that when it is time to dive into all of that, I’ve got you. I’ve been planning a really incredible workshop behind the scenes that I am so excited about. Until then, sit down, chill out, stop thinking about what you want to build, and know that pausing will actually stoke the flames of creativity & vision. 

Tomorrow is Solstice, the longest night of the year and the original Christmas. We keep our kids home from school and live by candle light, celebrate our year, do a spiral walk and make head wreaths. I may even attempt cinnamon buns 🌀. 

If we don’t voluntarily pause, the Goddess will do it for us. Well played Goddess, well played.

We are entering the potent portal of Winter Solstice.  It’s the longest night of the year, and with it comes an energy of being in the dark.

On the 21st, relish in sacred space and allow yourself to go into the darkness.

Do this any way you can:
-Take social media off your phone
-Save your to-do’s for another day
-Turn off your phone for a few hours
-Turn off the lights and live by candlelight for the night

Or swipe to follow a simple ritual you can do solo or with loved ones.

If you have kids, adjust this ritual to include them.  I always honor Yule by pulling my kids from school, being outside during the daylight, spending time by fire and candlelight, opening magical earthly gifts, and visiting our land to sing to the trees.  Honoring this day with my children is one of my favorite parts of motherhood.

Tell me how you will honor the Winter Solstice in the comments or send me a DM - I’d love to know! 🕯️
Happy Solstice my loves! What are you calling in during this rebirth portal?

If you honor the birth of Jesus at Christmas, do not forget about Mary, a powerful Priestess who stood in her highest power and stepped confidently into her destiny to be a part of a great lineage of people who came to ground love and light on the planet.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Remember that tyrannical leaders painted her as a weak, meak, virginal bystander when it was her sovereignty, power and strength that makes the story of Christmas so rich.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
May we all remember that Yeshua wasn’t the Christ meaning “Anointed One” until he was anointed by Mary Magdalene, a Priestess in the same lineage as her Mother in Law.

Yeshua AND Mary Magdalene together came to show that God exists within all of us and symbolize the heiros gamos (when the sacred masculine meets the sacred feminine) both within us and between people and we don’t need a church, money or fancy titles to commune with the Cosmos - just our bodies, love and presence.

Yeshua was a disrupter. He shook up the status quo and put himself and his family in a lot of danger. Mother Mary could have followed her motherly instincts and told him to fit in, to tone it down, but she was clear on her mission, to love and support this man and to trust in his life purpose, just as she had trusted in hers.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The stories we hear shape our views on life, love, motherhood and how we show up. Let’s all start to share the truth of this moment and this life.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Merry Christmas.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

Last night we sat around the Christmas table with a Menorah at the center, and I just felt our ancestors smiling. We take it for granted, but this level of acceptance and honoring of different religions amongst families is new in the grand scheme of history. My Grandfather, a theologian and preacher’s kid, opened the grace with “Dear Father and Mother God” which made my Priestess heart so happy, and I’m sure was a nod to me and my practices. We did our own telling of the Christmas story on Christmas Eve in lieu of Church which included Miriam’s (Mother Mary) Priestess training. And the overlap of rituals with Solstice.

There is space for all of it.

PS. Can we talk about @lisaclarkjenksdesign mantel design!? It’s next level festive over here.

If you want to change your life in 2023, don’t miss this step…

First, the only life change I approve is becoming more of yourself. More expressed, clearer on what you want, really going for it, prioritizing deep nourishment and being fully resourced. I am hosting a sacred & strategic workshop in the new year that I am REALLY excited about, which I’ll be sharing about tomorrow. 

But we can’t do that until we’ve processed where we’ve been. Over the next 5 days, I’m going to be here to check in with you around 2022 - what worked, and what didn’t.

Today, I invite you to ask yourself: how am I, really? This is a question that I learned from @jeanshinodabolen that we hold as the center of our Holy Woman community. Women are trained to stay on the surface and not be real about what’s happening, but we have to go deeper. We have to get honest about how we REALLY are. Even if it’s just with yourself.

How are you, really? Feel free to share below.

Who is committed to doing these 5 things everyday 🙋🏼‍♀️? 

If you have a hard time imagining a big & beautiful vision for your life it’s probably because you feel like sh*+ 😬. Our body chemistry impacts our ability to dream big, so before we all dive into 2023 big dreaming, we have to prepare the vessel.

(I’ve been spending the past month dreaming into and creating the perfect New Years workshop, can’t wait to tell you about it tomorrow! And I want all of us to get the most out of it.)

I personally am feeling puffy, sluggish and grumpy after eating & drinking so much (and spending so much time with my kids 🤪). Our Christmas was amazing AND my body & soul need some TLC.

Have any to add to this list?

Calling all rule breakers, trail blazers, black sheep and walking oxy morons! As we cross the threshold into the New Year we are thinking about all of the things we want, and most of us are probably also thinking “but can I really have ALL of that?”

Can I be successful in my career and be a present mom?

Can I have a dependable lifelong relationship and the hottest sex of my life?

Can I have a life of travel adventure and wildness and also be grounded in the land?

Can I be deeply devoted to my sacred practice and also have a fancy wardrobe and enjoy five star hotels?

Not only can you - creating a life that supports All of YOU contributes to the evolution of this planet.

Our conditioning teaches us that we have to follow the rules, be one thing and cut off parts of ourselves in order to be a good citizen, a good Mom or a good coworker. This belief as a brainwashing tool that has been put inside of us in order to keep us small.

Weaving together seemingly conflicting parts of what we want, is what actually creates freedom. 

So, this year I am excited to invite you into a very special ceremony and workshop to put a stake in the ground around standing for making space for all parts of you.

Join me for 

ALL OF ME 2023
On the Day of the Goddess
Friday January 13th
$99 (invite all the friends you want to your home & ticket purchase can be applied towards any of my programs in 2023)
Sign up in my bio

I can’t wait ❤️

Let’s check in around your Body!

I know this is a triggering topic. Women’s bodies have been tossed around and been under scrutiny for centuries.

This is about reclaiming your body for you, but that can’t happen until you get real about how you feel.

This isnt about matching a cultural beauty ideal - this is about your home, and having a home that works well and that can support your dreams this year.

Many of us take better care of our cars and our dogs than we do our bodies 🥺. That used to be me.

For a long time I was obsessed with not falling prey to the pressure of looking a certain way that I saw eating whatever I wanted and not working out as a revolutionary act. But the truth was I felt sick, lethargic and down most of the time because I wasn’t taking care of my body. I didn’t have enough energy to fuel my dreams, I didn’t have enough energy for my kids, and I certainly wasn’t feeling feminine and sensual which not only impacted my marriage, but my general sense of joy in my life.

This year I did a total 180 and I can’t tell you how amazing I feel. We will be coming up with your vision for your body in All of Me 2023, but before we can forge a future we have to look back.

How are you feeling in your body? Feel free to share below.

If you feel stuck at a certain “level” in your life, if you feel like you’re holding yourself back, if you feel exhausted & frustrated (Who’s DONE with this 🙋🏼‍♀️) I want to share this really important truth with you.

This concept completely changed the course of my life, and it’s so important that you understand it.

We are not meant to feel exhausted all the time. We are not meant to hate our bodies. We are not meant to feel like we’re walking on egg shells around our partner, that we need to tone it down for our friends or pretend to be someone we’re not for our families. We are not meant to feel guilty for doing something kind and nourishing for ourselves.

We are meant to feel FREE. Wild. In love with our bodies. Creative. Like we can change the world.

You are a force of nature.

But our society wants women to be exhausted robots who are constantly worried about what others think because then we are more likely to do what others want us to do.

This isn’t your personality, or a flaw, this is an *infection*.

Part of this infection is that it convinces us that’s it’s who we are. And we blame ourselves.

I’m not smart enough
I don’t have any willpower 
I’m not beautiful enough
I don’t have what she has
I’m too old
I’m too young

None of that is true. That’s the infection.

You don’t need to become someone different, you just need to heal the infection.

When you remove the brainwashing, what is left is a supernova of a soul made human. A miraculous work of art. A Joan of Arc in modern clothes.

You are already a masterpiece. Your infection has just short circuited your wiring.

How do we heal?

We get Sacred.

We connect with the source of who we truly are. We filter out the lies by seeing our truth so clearly. We connect with the Great Mother and feel unconditional love so we aren’t looking for love in all the wrong places. We experience magic that will blow you right open. We connect with the source of your power. We Remember.

I’m here to do the inner work of women’s freedom, which led me to being a practitioner of the Sacred Feminine because it is the antidote to what ails us… continued in carousel.

📸 @workplaybranding at The Tor for my ordination.

A little Planet PSA! Also, when I say “really go for it” I do NOT mean, hustle, push or over work. I mean be your whole self, be bold, do your best idea first, take a risk, take a left turn, break the rules.

Love you. This is going to be FUN!

WHAT A YEAR 😭😭😭. 2021 was the hardest year of my life, and I dug deep to make massive changes in 2022.

I can’t honestly remember having a year that was full of so much growth, so much change, so many risks, and so many HOLY SHIT AM I REALLY GOING TO DO THIS moments.

It was deeply uncomfortable, scary AF and absolutely filled to the brim with heart exploding, revolutionary, joyful moments.

I had to make a big departure from my comfortable, predictable patterns by doing some deep inner work and fully surrender to not knowing how things were going to turn out. What a rush.

If you’re curious about how to do this for yourself, I’ll be teaching exactly how to make this shift in All Of Me 2023.

Happy New Years my loves!! Thanks for being on this ride with me.

#happynewyear #consciousnewyear #newyearsintentions

Happy New Year my loves! It’s very late here, but I have an urgent message.

After having an epic New Year’s Eve with deep sharing, card pulls, energy clearing on the living room floor, too much champagne, so much laughter & love and staying up til 1am, today was hard!

Too much sugar (me)
So many meltdowns (my kids)
A child threw up in the car
And I started going into a fear swirl about the year and immediately started doing the OPPOSITE of the intention I set last night.

I could have said I f’d up, but now I know this is how it works. Growth happens by contrast.

The biggest lesson I learned from having the best year of my life is, there are just as many hard days, just as many heart breaks, just as many gut wrenching challenges - but because I chose to be on my Soul’s Path, I know all of those challenges are shaping me into the woman I’m meant to be.

Being our best selves - our soul-selves is not measured by good days, it is measured by authenticity, integrity, surrender and starting over.

Over and over and over again.

Who needed to hear this? And maybe you want to save this for when you need a reminder ❤️

I love you. I can’t wait to do 2023 together.

Don’t forget to ask yourself THIS important question as you’re doing your intention setting.

Was this helpful?

Are your intentions and goals for 2023 what you really REALLY want? Or they just what most people do?

And by most people, I mean your family, your friends, your industry, the culture you’re in…

A lot of us got on auto pilot because we are operating from our conditioning and blending in.

But it is so important to no longer look outside of yourself or what you *should want but instead look INSIDE yourself.

How do you that? You get sacred.

Ceremony, ritual, guided meditations, sacred feminine mythology - these are all ways to access your deep, feminine truth.

If you are looking to get to the core of what you really want in 2023 and you have a tendency to look outside of yourself for permission - I hope you’ll join me for All Of Me 2023 ❤️. If you want this year to be different, you need to approach it differently. 

I see SO many women going down the clearly laid out path, mindlessly following “what is done”, afraid to get out of auto-pilot because they’re worried they’ll blow up their lives.  Its ok to take a left turn. You have no idea how much more fulfilling your life will be.

When have you felt conflicted between what most people do and what you really want? I would love to hear your story below ❤️.

I have a secret to tell you - every single new thing I did last year, I was absolutely petrified to do.

Try to pull off a 100 person retreat at my house? Was I out of my mind?

Invite 17 women to invest big money with me as their mentor? Never gonna happen.

Stand for body healing and convince women of the power of ancestral healing & coffee enemas to heal their bodies? So strange, Sarah.

Launch a global online Church to the Sacred Feminine? Do women even want that?

But my conviction came when I connected with my WHY.

I know that what women need to feel free is to know that they are divine beings.

I am extremely passionate about sacred women being paid, honored and respected just as much as doctors lawyers and bankers.

I was dying for women to get off of zoom and in nature to do their sacred work.

I experienced firsthand about the life-changing impact of taking incredible care of my body and healing deeply seeded brainwashing.

I had to put my fears aside and do it for the change I wanted to see in my community.

And oh my GODDESS! The laughter, The tears, The long thank you emails, the stories of freedom, new clarity, new friendships, it all came back to me tenfold.

If your dreams scare the shit out of you. If you are afraid to go for it. If you’re worried you will fail, I hope you’ll join me for All Of Me 2023. We’re going to work through that together.

Love you all so much. What is feeling really scary to you right now?

I need you to know that you are already the woman who has it all. You are already so talented, so intentional and so creative. You have everything it takes to create your dream life.

You’ve just been brainwashed to believe wanting those things makes you a bad person.

I used to believe that wanting to have a great life, own my big energy and go after what I want, means I’m vain, selfish or a narcissist (and not only did I believe it but women also told me to my face, Tra la). And I know I’m not alone.

This brainwashing keeps us in a cycle of living small, of doing what’s expected of us, of never doing anything that may make others uncomfortable.

At the beginning of 2022, I decided to do the deep work around cultivating my soul-self, The version of me that was unencumbered by my conditioning and our society. Through sacred practice and strategy I radically changed who I was, which radically changed my financial success, my body, my marriage, motherhood, my friendships…

I created All of Me 2023 to be a Sacred and strategic activation of your soul self, so every part of your life can change.

PS. I know that baked into what most women want contributes to the thriving of everyone around her, because women’s hearts are so big, and when we have overflow, we shower it around generously.

If you want this to be the year you are deeply nourished, make great money, have an incredible marriage, have deeply meaningful days, and a sacred life you have to heal this brainwashing and know your soul-self. 

You in?

A Witch: from the root word, “wise one” also a Woman In Total Control of Herself (cc @devonmcole ) - not to be confused with Wiccan, which is a certain subset of Witches.

Any person who looks to nature, the moon and the stars to reveal the great mystery of life, is a Witch in my book.

I believe that we, as Mothers, deserve to know that having a full, beautiful, dynamic, adventurous life isn’t impossible or something we need to give up in order to be a good Mom.

When I became a Mother, I felt, in this day and age, I should feel more freedom and flexibility to create my own life - but instead I felt stuck in a box.

I felt the heaviness of a paradigm of Motherhood that promotes a culture of exhaustion, over giving, and constantly sidelining my needs for my kids and partner. There were all of these internalized, unspoken expectations around parts of me and my life that I had to give up in order to be a good mom.

Before I became a mother I was ambitious, outspoken, sexy, adventurous, and had a full amazing life.

When I became a mother 9 years ago, I felt like I needed to give up all of these things that made me feel alive, and like ME. I lost my freedom, I lost my sensuality, I lost my joy, I lost my flexibility, I lost my space, I lost my creativity, I lost my elegance, I lost my style, I lost my wildness, I lost my sense of adventure. I didn’t know who I was, or if I was going to ever feel like myself ever again. I felt trapped in the expectations of motherhood.

And I kept asking myself: Do I need to just get used to this new normal? Or does this new normal just not work for me?

Most of us have been led to believe that losing 95% of who we are is part of what’s needed to raise children, and I vehemently disagree.

I have spent the past 9 years leaning into the possibility that I could be an incredible mother to my three beautiful children and also create a successful company, travel regularly, feel sexy and elegant, have a strong sense of who I am, have deep female friendships, feel in love with and attracted to my husband, and cultivate a strong connection with the divine.

There is no one-way to do Motherhood, and I’m not here to to teach you how to have my life, but I created a course for you to step into creating a life that is a true reflection of your soul, and not just built around the needs of your role.

Sovereign Mother is only $99 (down from $333) until Friday. If you are a mom, and you want to feel alive again, this is for you.

If you are looking for a retreat, ongoing community, monthly ceremony, deep immersive experiences, or a mastermind for spiritual ambitious women, AND you are looking to integrate sacred feminine wisdom into your every day life so you can create a rich, sexy and meaningful existence - I think you would love everything we have going on in 2023.

I used to be the woman who hit snooze for 90 minutes until my kids were jumping on me in bed to get them breakfast.

When it comes to our bodies oftentimes we find ourselves caught between a rock and a hard place. We don’t want to be caught up in the patriarchal swirl of weight loss, but we also don’t want to feel like sh*t in our bodies all the time.

And every time we think about getting healthy, we get worried that we’re going down a slippery slope of self-hatred and selling out to the fictitious cultural ideal of beauty.

We may wonder “isn’t loving my body as it is the most evolved path?”

That is our current paradigm of being a woman in a body. And in this paradigm we can never win.

But I believe in a new paradigm. A paradigm that has nothing to do with cultural standards and everything to do with our soul’s expression.

This is a post for the married couples with kids on Valentine’s Day.

You may be so bogged down by family responsibilities that you don’t even remember what it’s like to be romantic with your partner. Who can relate? 

Here’s what’s real: our culture has normalized having a mediocre, romantic-less marriage when you’ve been together for a long time and have kids. Because we’ve been taught that this is normal, we don’t cultivate our romantic connection. In fact, we are conditioned to believe that taking time away from our kids in order to tend to our romantic relationship is selfish and hurts our children.  We are also led to believe that it’s something that should just emerge naturally - causing it to never happen.

@Jonathanbrajtbord and I have been together 17 years, married for 12 this June. We have 3 kids 8, 7 and 4. He’s a physician, I’m a CEO, we’re renovating our house, and have very full lives. We really know what’s it’s like to feel like there’s no space for us.

Jonathan and I used to have a mediocre, even toxic marriage. We were like hostile roommates and full of resentment. We were always in competition and wanted different things.

I could see how not having a deep, loving and romantic connection with Jonathan made me feel like I was missing out on a big part of life. I could feel how I was missing out on the fuel that would make me feel alive, happy and in love with my life.

Cultivating romantic love when your married with kids is paramount to your thriving. Do the work and be different.

After being in deep devotion to healing our marriage and tending to our romantic relationship, it feels like Jonathan and I are on our second (or third?) marriage to each other. We operate completely differently. We show up as our best selves. We are creating an epic life together. We are deeply attracted to each other. And we make a lot of time for our romantic relationship. Jonathan and our love, is my number one source of fuel now, even though our marriage used to be our biggest drain.

People can change, marriages can change, both people need to be willing to do the work.

Maybe this Valentine’s Day you both can commit to doing things differently?

The moment that this new health journey started for me was when I landed in the hospital with a “complete heart block” due to acute lyme, which I later found out from @SinclairKennally of @detoxrejuvenation, was caused by mold and heavy metal toxicity in my body.

I knew that being in the hospital was an initiation and a wake up call for me not only on a physical level in my body but on a spiritual & emotional level in my life.

One of the patterns I identified when I spent a week in the hospital was that I often took myself right up to the edge of exhaustion before getting the support I needed. I was trying to operate like a stay at home mom with a full-time job. For me this looked like not having my nanny stay past 3, saying it’s fine when Jonathan has to come home at 6:30 or 7 a few nights in a row, saying it’s fine when a team member can’t meet a deadline and I just do it myself while I’m trying to make the kids dinner, offering to stay home with a sick kid every time, so Jonathan can go to work.

I COULD do it. But I didn’t have to… my system felt comfortable with being just on the edge of depletion at all times when it came to Motherhood.

When my body shut down I knew I needed to take a whole life approach to healing. Not only did I need to look at what was happening on the inside physically, but I had to take a hard look at how I was living my life was contributing to my body shutting down.

And I knew the changes I needed to make were going to feel way over the top.

We shifted a lot in our everyday life. Jonathan is now home at five every day and says no to a lot of night meetings. Our nanny stays until 5 at least twice a week. When a child is sick we trade off.

Now when Jonathan is away, I line up the most beautiful support. I invite myself over to my friend’s house for dinner, I plan a girls night out, my parents often come to take care of the kids for a night and I’ll even do something extra juicy like organizing a massage in The Temple. I set up playdates. I’m still tired but I’m not depleted, and that is a massive win for me.

Our culture normalizes mothers being completely depleted, have you normalized it too?

Tired of feeling like a frumpy, tired, washed up Mom!?

Let’s talk about the abundance of energies that are happening today for you to celebrate!

With the Spring (Vernal) Equinox, today holds the frequency of balance and harmony as the hours of day and night are of equal length and after today the light will continue to expand, growing more frequent until the Summer Solstice on June 21st.

This sacred day also marks the threshold of spring, welcoming the opportunity for new beginnings and the fertile potential of planting new seeds of ideas, dreams, and desires (as well as actual seeds since this is the beginning of the planting season). 

In Celtic tradition it is also known as Ostara, which is a celebration of renewal and rebirth, honoring the Goddess Eostre. Many cultures around the world celebrate spring festivals and holidays such as Easter and Passover, around the time of the equinox. For example, Easter always falls on the first Sunday after the first full moon which happens after the March equinox. 

These ancient earth-based spring celebrations, rituals, and traditions influence the Easter Traditions that many people continue to celebrate today. The words East and Easter were both named after Ostara, referencing the rising sun in the east and the increased sunlight and the beginning of springtime. Ostara is typically depicted with bunnies and eggs as they represent the fertility of springtime.

This equinox also starts alongside the new year of the zodiac wheel, which begins with Aries and brings in a season of fiery passion, forward momentum and aligned action.

Celebrating seasonal holidays such as this is a beautiful way of deeply connecting with the Earth, which will help you to feel, embrace and honor your wild, feminine soul. Which is exactly the work we do inside of Holy Woman.

Walking this path means being a living embodiment, where we channel this intuitive wisdom that has always existed within us and allow it to guide our daily actions. Integrating the Sacred Feminine into your everyday life is how you acknowledge, accept, own and reclaim all parts of yourself back into wholeness so you can live with internal as well as external liberation. It is the remembrance that you are not just this one thing but rather are all encompassing. You are many faces, each with its own essence that yearns and needs to be fully expressed.

You are the bold warrior, the sensual seductress, the loving nurturer and the grounded wise woman. 

The Sacred Feminine is not something separate from you. She lives within you, through you and as you in your everyday life.

Can you feel how it’s time to weave her back in?

Finding a supportive community who gets what you’re going through is not a luxury, it’s a necessity that will help you navigate the various phases of your life that you inevitably will go through.

When you make it a habit of adding women to your life who are in similar phases to you, it takes the pressure off the people in your life who aren’t in that phase or who don’t resonate with some of the same things you do. It’s not that you have to break up with them, it’s just that they can’t be your everything for every situation. 

It’s about prioritizing the habit of meeting new people, making new friends who are on the same page as you. It’s not always easy but the benefits far outweigh that initial discomfort of putting yourself out there. 
 And we have to remember that this isn’t the playground anymore and life is no longer a popularity contest. Sometimes it might be awkward to make new friends, sometimes it won’t.

Maybe if you seem awkward, the other person will think, “yes! someone who is as quirky as me!” and you have that instant comfort with each other. Most women want to make new friends and most women aren’t brave enough to do it. I guarantee that if you make the first move, she will be eternally grateful.

And if you want to get connected to other magical women who are committed to their own Sacred life, and yours, you can join us inside of Holy Woman.

What does your life need to look like in order for you to experience total freedom?​​​​​​​​​
A life of liberation, of being in your authentic power and having the choice to follow your own truth looks different for everybody.

I have created a life of freedom, of being in my authentic power and that looks one way for me, but the way I do my life is not the way you need to do your life.

Everyone’s expression of freedom and being in choice is as unique as our fingerprint. I am not here to teach you how to live a life like mine. I’m here to teach you to create a life that looks like yours.

I believe that the best way to learn what freedom looks and feels like for you, and then to have the courage to create a life that reflects that (in a culture that attempts to oppress women in doing that very thing) is to remember that you are a sacred being and a holy woman.

When women integrate the Sacred Feminine into our everyday lives, we create a connection with our soul. Our soul contains the blueprint of what freedom, authentic power, and ultimate choice means for you. It also gives you the courage to create it.

This is why educating women on the sacred feminine and holding ceremony is at the center of my work.

What blueprint of authentic freedom and sovereign choice is your soul pointing you toward?

Though I grew up with a very open-minded and positive experience of Christianity, I couldn’t help but feel there was a massive piece of the puzzle that was missing.

Where were all the women!?

This absence of my gender in these sacred stories I grew up with had an effect on me and I believe it has an effect on all of us, even if it is subconscious. When we don’t have examples of independent, strong, outspoken, sacred women, we can’t rise to our own potential. And when the only stories we’re told about women in church are about a Virgin and a Whore, we can’t help but embody the beliefs that our sensuality and wildness are evil.

It wasn’t always this way…In indigenous cultures all over the world that pre-dated Christianity, the stories were about the Sacred Mother and the Sacred Father.

With the respect people had for the Goddess as the creator, this translated to respect of women as creators. We were honored as life givers, herbalists, healers, wisdom keepers, and the doorway to other realms. Our wildness and sensuality were encouraged and we were taught that our bodies were sacred vessels meant to be treated with the utmost respect.

It is so important to understand that the Sacred Feminine didn’t just naturally fall out of favor. It was deliberately and violently removed on purpose to control the masses and make people (especially women) fear and reject their innate power. We were taught to no longer think for ourselves, to become who our father wanted us to be, to give everything we have to our children, to say yes to everything, to never make anyone uncomfortable, and to prioritize fitting in over self-expression.

I’ve now led thousands of women from being scared or weirded out by the Sacred Feminine, to using these structures in their daily life and marrying them with practical strategy. You should see what these women are up to now. Whoa. Complete transformation from growing successful companies, to getting out of dead-end relationships, to completely changing their relationship with their bodies.

What is your relationship with the Sacred Feminine? Are you curious to re-acquaint yourself with it? Let me know in the comments!

Did you know that during the burning times in Europe - as they were stripping away the Sacred Feminine from the culture, they were also systematically removing women’s access to money? Have you ever considered the pressure you feel to live up to everybody’s expectations, to stay the course of traditional success, to be the perfect mom, friend or daughter — isn’t the life you came here to live?

That the roles you play, the job you have and everything you are to everybody else has actually nothing to do with who you really are? Or that the feeling of imposter syndrome is there not because you aren’t incredibly talented, but because your true purpose isn’t being activated?

I used to get constant messages in Ceremony that I was meant to normalize the Sacred Feminine in a very Puritan New England. I kept seeing myself being a Priestess and building a modern day Temple.

But as the primary breadwinner back then, and a mother of two under two, I didn’t think it was the best time to step into my life’s purpose. Being a Priestess didn’t seem like smart business decision 😬.

Until one night, from out of nowhere, I heard…
“I won’t give you the life you want until you do the work you came here to do.”

Fuck.

Do you know how much I wanted to be a Priestess?
0%

Do you know how much my Soul KNEW that this was what I was meant to do?
100000%

Incredibly inconvenient, but I started putting a plan together anyway because I was tired of following the rules that kept me overworked and under satisfied.

Fast forward to last year when I stood in my huge field with 75 other women doing ceremony on the sacred land that I steward.

I watched them come alive, make lifelong friends, remember who they are, and step onto their life’s mission.

It’s a weekend that changed me forever because it was THE THING I came here to do. And we’re doing it again on the Fall Equinox. 

Every step that brought me to this place felt impossible. 
Every risk I had to take made me feel like I was going to die. 
Every win felt like a miracle.

But I know that I have the life I want because I am doing what I came here to do.

And if you know that this is true for you - I am here to initiate you into your path.

If you are called to finally do THE THING you came here to do…

If you know that it’s time to stop pretending to be someone you’re not…

Then I would love to have you at Emerge.

Humans have evolved to learn through story and make sense of our lives and identities through metaphor. 

This is why religion and spiritual practices have been at the core of human existence, since we started walking this planet - it’s how we learn to see ourselves in the world.

So it was really smart of the few men who got together and decided they wanted to control a mass amount of people. What did they do? They changed the stories.

I’m sure they thought - how can we get women to stop being disruptive, powerful, revolutionaries? We will elevate the symbol of being a sexless, silent, peace keeping mother.

But that isn’t who Mother Mary was at all. 

When we learn about religion and spirituality from a sacred feminine perspective, we take in metaphor that supports our truth as Women and we remember who we truly are.

I’ve had a long time struggle with feeling like Im a bad Mom because I am constantly comparing myself to the Patriarchal ideal of Motherhood - which I am not built for.

When I began to look for archetypes of mothers that inspired me - Mother Mary, Inana and Mary Magdalene to name a few - I leaned into Mothering in a way that felt right for me. 

Happy Mother’s Day! You’re a powerful, multidimensional, wild Mother. ❤️

This isn’t true for me anymore (although it used to be), and I don’t want this to be true for you.

Here’s why I love Moondays:

After a very full, very happy weekend with my kids, it’s time for me to have some Sarah time. Did you know that you can use the moon cycle as a tool for manifesting your deepest desires and creating the life you’re actually meant to live? 

Swipe for a step-by-step guide on How to Manifest with the Moon. 👉🏼

Working with the energy and wisdom of the moon is an ancient Sacred Feminine practice that was once part of our everyday lives, so it’s not surprising that you’re drawn to learning more about it.

While the Sun is a masculine energy (it rises and sets at basically the same time everyday and stays in one zodiac sign for almost a month), the Moon is a feminine energy that rises and sets at very different times everyday. The moon goes through a zodiac sign every 2.5 days making its energy ever changing – it’s mysterious and instills wildness and magic.

Here’s what’s cool: The Sun goes through a whole cycle in 365 days, while the Moon goes through a whole cycle in 29.5 days. Meaning it goes from New to Full to New again in less than a calendar month. We have 13 Moon cycles in a year, which is why 13 is such a sacred number (and why the patriarchy rebranded it as an unlucky number).

This is why I love working with Sacred Feminine principles. Because built into this “woo woo” business of the moon, there is a very practical process of personal growth that keeps us honest, accountable, on track, and intentional about our life and where we’re going. Working with the cycle is the best way to keep you moving forward if you feel like you’re stuck on the hamster wheel. 

If you want a group of women to do this with, join Holy Woman. We meet every New Moon for Ceremony to set intentions and do some magic to help us get super clear on what we need to do in order to step into our fully expressed self and the best version of who we are. One day I walked into my therapist’s office where the remnants of a sacred circle from the night before were strewn on the living room floor. I had a full body “Remembering” of being in Ceremony. Since that day I have devoted my life to creating spaces for women to have their own remembering and normalizing the presence of the Sacred Feminine in our culture.

This experience led me to a decade of studying, apprenticing & eventually becoming an Ordained Priestess in the 13 Moon Mystery School. My personal sacred practice weaves together the mysteries of Ancient Avalon, Earth-based practices of my Celtic and Germanic ancestry, the Feminine Path of Mary Magdalene, and the Ancient Egyptian practices of Anointing.

My genius is in creating a sacred container that allows you to talk directly to your Soul, your fully expressed self, the truest version of you — and then guiding you to create strategies, environment, and structures that will allow you to create the life you’re actually meant to live.

I hold a clear & unapologetic vision for the world where highly respected, highly successful, highly sought-after Sacred Women are EVERYWHERE. Walking in their true power. Totally liberated.

I am an avid skinny dipper, travel often, love fancy restaurants, talk to trees, and am the CEO of a global spiritual coaching & lifestyle company. I am a walking oxymoron, a rule breaker, and live an out-of-the-box life in a very “in the box” part of the world. I believe that our lives get to be a masterpiece and you have the ability to create whatever you want.

The truth?

You get to have it all.

We’ve been conditioned to believe that we’re only supposed to be one way but this is what the Sacred Feminine teaches us. That we have range, that we have many different desires inside of us and not only is it normal for you to have those feelings, it’s natural for you to express them.

Over the past 10 years, I’ve worked with tens of thousands of women. I have heard countless stories of misery, hating their body, fighting with their partner, feeling rejected by their parents, feeling lost in their career, feeling stressed about money…

When they come to me for advice, I always ask the same question first

“What do you want?”

I swear to the Goddess, 99.9% of the time they say 

“I don’t know”

And this doesn’t surprise me at all because I know from my studies in the internalized oppression of women and how our culture has deliberately impacted women’s psychology - we have been brainwashed to not know what we want.

That’s messed up right?

But my love, if you do not know what you want, if you do not know where you are going, if you do not have a destination on the map, you will walk in circles your entire life.

AND you will be hypnotized into helping other people get what they want, or being who other people want you to be.

That’s exactly what our oppressive culture wants.

So, if you are on the path of being happy, if you want to create more joy in your life, if you want to be prosperous and wild and free, and also stable and safe, your number one priority should be to unbrainwash yourself to know what you want.

Drop a 🐆if you know what you want and tell me what that is…

🎥 from @caitscudder ‘s mastermind weekend by @monicajustesen

How many of you are living your life according to someone else’s rules or are walking along a path that you KNOW deep down inside is just not meant for you?

If this is you…I need you to know that you don’t have to keep living this way.

Your life is yours and you get to choose how to live it.

When you step off the train of who you “should” be and get onto the locomotive of who you are meant to be…you’ll find more and more people that are on this same journey and are here to inspire, empower and support you.

Which is exactly what happens to the women inside of Holy Woman.
They become who they were always meant to be and find their community of like-hearted soul sisters.

We have been conditioned to feel that we need to be strong all the time. We feel this constant need to be on guard, looking for war after war to fight which makes us feel like we always have to have our battle armor on.

We find ourselves either on the attack, using our words to cut or on the defense where we avoid living fully in order to protect ourselves.

The energy if this moon cycle & what I’ve come to learn is that when I allow myself to expand and create a frequency of calm, softness, and joy, I am (more often then not) met by people who will set down their swords… and then I don’t have to be on guard with my sword. 

My invitation for you today as we head into the first holiday weekend of summer, is to drop your sword, pull off your helmet and walk lightly into a softer life until there is no one left for you to fight.

That is how we create the Eden that our heart and soul desire to live in everyday.

What war do you keep fighting that you are so ready to be done with?

Tell me below. 🛡️

If you long for a life filled with meaning, prosperity and joy but you’re feeling stuck – let’s talk about why “manifesting” isn’t working for you and what to try instead.

Most manifestation practices focus on getting clear about what you want, but leave out a really important part of the process, which is around knowing what your Soul actually came here to do – or in other words, what you’re meant for. 

The work is actually about calling in the life that is meant for you – what your Soul wants – not what your conditioning has brainwashed you to think you want.

If you’re ready to discover what your Soul’s mission is, then I want to introduce you to a fun, efficient, deeply transformative practice… 

Ceremony.

I’m talking about a very specific type of Sacred Feminine Ceremony (no drugs) that only a handful of people on the planet know how to hold. 

And I am lucky enough to be one of those people.

After years of transforming very slowly in my therapy and coaching practices (even though that healing was extremely helpful and necessary), I finally experienced rapid growth and transformation – it was almost immediate when I sat in Ceremony with my mentor. Over the past 10 years, I have been immersing myself in the process, apprenticing & training and mastering my skills. 

When you come into Ceremony, you will experience an almost automatic shift from identifying with your personality, or who you should be, into feeling the truth of your Soul.

And when you can fully hear your Soul, you have access to unlimited creativity, incredible bravery, and crystal clear vision about what YOU really want and where you are meant to go.

If you’ve been in Ceremony with me before, share in the comments what you’ve experienced! There is no better way for women who are on the fence to understand what we’re doing here, than to hear it directly from you.

👀 If manifesting hasn’t worked for you, if you feel stuck, or you’re just curious and want to see what this is all about, comment MORE to sign up for my free Ceremony & Workshop on June 7 – Women Who Want More.

PS - When you come to the live Workshop, you’ll be entered to win one of my biggest giveaways – details in stories!

HOUSE UPDATE: We moved into a rental on the other side of town when we started the renovation on our home in December. The truth was, I was miserable. I didn’t think I was going to miss the land as much as I did, but what I discovered was that living where we do is a huge part of how we parent our children, and how we structure our whole days. 

At the end of April, we moved out of our rental and into the Moon Lodge - my temple where we hold ceremony in Holy Woman. I immediately felt happier and more at home. The Moon Lodge is one huge open space with a single tiny bedroom, 1.5 baths & a tiny kitchen. The kids are all sleeping together in the bedroom and Jonathan and I have our bed (and closet!) in the main room. 

We are loving it - we have only what we need, very few toys and limited wardrobes (hardest for me). 

We have been holding our ceremonies outside in the Sacred Grove during these warm nights, and we are starting to renovate the barn to have ceremonies in the barn during the winter until we can move back into our house in about a year. 

Giving up my office space wasn’t easy, but I’m learning how to integrate my work, and the children more, and there’s nothing better than witnessing them waking up in the morning and playing outside or going down to the lake.

For most people home is their house. For me, home is my land.

I’ve been crying for weeks, anticipating today - the day we dropped out little boy at overnight camp for two weeks.

But the tears aren’t because I’m nervous, but because of my overwhelming joy and relief that I know he is going to THRIVE at camp.

If you’re new here (hi 👋🏼) Marshall has been a major intiation in my life. When he was younger, he bit me 20 times a day, got kicked out of a few pre schools, never slept, was very explosive all day, everyday. 

I was exhausted, my nervous system shot, but mostly worried about what was plaguing this little boy.

Over the years I have gone all in on figuring out this boy and giving him what he needs to become the best version of himself. This is what we’ve done (I could write a whole book on this, so I encourage you to do your own research and go deeper where you’re called).

1. Mother/Son therapy with a play therapist when he was 3, every week for 6 months. This is what repaired our bond after my PPD.
2. Forest School
3. Encouraged physical risks at home - jumping off couches etc.
4. Chiropractic - his misalignment was contributing to the way he was taking in the world, and the way his brain processed it. He was working way harder than he needed to to do basic things.
5. Read “The Spirited Child” and had all the grandparents read it.
6. Created a SOLID routine.
7. He slept on our floor for two straight years for some solid nervous system re-regulation. 
8. Sports - I didn’t want to be the “activity mom” but when he started playing sports 4-5 days a week, WOW game changer.
9. We let him express his emotions in appropriate environments, we don’t try to fix it, we just let him get it out.
10. Music on all the time. His favorite is @aylanereo 
11. Ion Foot bath - draws out toxins, we did 3 days a week for a few months and noticed a massive difference. Thanks @detoxrejuvenation.
12. Talking about past lives - my Priestess self intuitively understood that this soul has not had it easy. I often ask him about his past lives, tune into them myself and tell him all the time, “in this life, it gets to be easy, you are safe and I will always be here.”

If you’re struggling, put in the work, it’s worth it.

It’s amazing what happens when you tend to women’s thriving. When you give them space to be in ceremony with each other. When you feed them nourishing food and allow space for crying, hands-on healing and introspection.

This type of work is innate to us. Even after just two hours of nourishing these feminine practices, dancing around a bonfire amongst the trees and under the stars like wild women, having deep and meaningful shares around the circle, women come more alive.

Our brilliance that has been dampened under layer after layer after layer of conditioning comes out in full, amplified, expansive power.

No wonder our culture has made us feel guilty for creating this level of nourishment for ourselves and weird for being in deep ceremony.

An alive, awake, nourished woman is a force of nature.

Our beloved bunny, Beatrice, died over the weekend, and I’ve been a total wreck. She died suddenly, and in a traumatic way, so it’s been… complex. 

My rational mind has been telling me that my sadness is disproportional to the situation - I want to convince myself that she was “just a rabbit” and I shouldn’t be so sad, but I am choosing to approach this from my Sacred Knowing, and the truth is, I believe she was so much more than that. 

Sometimes seeing with your Sacred Knowing, can feel a bit “out there” but remember, we have all been brainwashed to believe that the unseen world is weird - when in fact - it’s where we source our power.

I was talking to my medium and friend @jeannestreetmedium and the soul of Beatrice came through right away. Jeanne (whom I have never talked to Beatrice about before) said that Beatrice came to her as an older woman - a wise, professor type - which is exactly how she felt to me when she was in Bunny form. Beatrice showed Jeanne the lifetimes we had together, and this journey in this lifetime was exactly how it was meant to be.

I believe that we travel in packs, that our souls reincarnate with the same group of souls, over and over again to learn lessons, and to clear karma. Before Beatrice, I never considered that a soul connection can show up in animal form, but now I am absolutely convinced that Beatrice and I have done many lifetimes together.

Beatrice‘s death opened up something in me, as any challenging initiation will if you let it. With the grief I felt with her passing, I was also able to feel all of the grief that I have numbed out to in this lifetime, and I believe many others before.

Jeanne told me that with Beatrice passing from this world through the veils, she took with her my old patterns and trauma that I have been holding, with her. 

And I feel really different today than I did before she died.

Choosing to see these difficult times through our sacred knowing does make it more intense, but making meaning out of it has helped me evolve and upgrade my system rather quickly.

We can choose to see life through our rational mind or through our sacred knowing… How have you chosen to see your pets?

Even though you’ve created the life you once dreamed of - you still feel like you’re on the hamster wheel.

When the oppressive culture wiped out the Sacred Feminine, women were no longer honored for our creativity, wisdom, and sacred arts (that required very little pushing because it was just a part of our natural ability) and brainwashed us to only produce the next generation of workforce and do unending labor…

2. We also lost our connection with the cycles of life - growth, ripeness, release and emptiness - that we see in the seasons, the cycle of the moon and our menstrual cycle.

We are not meant to be in “growth” all the time.

Even though I am an Ordained Priestess of the Sacred Feminine, I live in the same world as you, and have been subject to the same brainwashing, so this challenge has been a big one for me.

I am a crammer. 

If I was a gardener, I would pack my garden beds so tight with plants that they suffocated each other, and had to fight for air and sun.

I was brainwashed to believe that this is what made me worthy - my capacity to hold A LOT had me holding a lot of different things at once. 

The result was that I had a lot of incredible things happening in my life, but I could not enjoy them. 

When I was in Italy with the Council, I was doing my own work around releasing my inner crammer, and facing all the fears I had about living in accordance with the Sacred Feminine cycle.

How I celebrate the life of a pet as a Priestess (save this for later when you need it, or send it to someone who may be about to lose a pet)… 

Our beloved bunny died over the weekend. Anyone who knew Beatrice said that she was a remarkable bunny. Super loving, playful and she had a big presence. She was a house Bunny, so she often felt like a small dog. We miss her terribly. 

I knew that the death of our first pet was going to set the tone for our kids on how they related with death, and I wanted to make it meaningful. 

As the Sacred Center on my family, I felt really grateful that I had the spiritual tools to move everyone through this sad time. I believe that all women know deep down how to make things sacred and guide our family and community through these thresholds, but here is what I did to jog your memory and give you permission to hold loss with a sacred lens next time you’re in the death portal.

1. I didn’t make light of it. It would have been easy to say - “it’s just a bunny”, or “we’ll get a new one!” Or “don’t be sad”. Instead we cried all day, told stories and honored our broken hearts.
2. I called in a circle of support - I called a few of my close friends who are death walkers and understand this portal for advice and to ground me.
3. When she was dying I brought her outside and sat with her, told her over and over that I love her, I am here, I’m sorry, you’re safe. Even if she didn’t understand my words, I know she felt my presence. I waited until I felt her soul release, and I energetically cleared the way for safe passage. I spoke words of love and gratitude as she left her body.
4. I wrapped her body in a little blanket and surrounded her with flowers. This helped her body feel like an altar and was less scary for the kids. All day the kids visited her body and added flowers and told her they loved her.
5. We cooked lunch over a fire - I knew that having a fire around the kids would help them move their feelings.

If you feel like you haven’t made the most out of your summer, here’s a Sacred Strategy for turning your summer around:

Today is the Full Moon in Aquarius and Lammas - the half way point between Summer Solstice and Fall Equinox. 

This Full Moon invites you to get clarity on your vision & Lammas is about ripening. So I believe that today is a powerful day to have radical clarity, and step into that vision immediately - here’s how…

Create some Sacred Space for yourself - light a candle, go outside, keep it simple. Get paper, matches & a pot.

📝 Answer these questions in your journal:

1. What would your perfect summer be? Where would you go? What would you do? Imagine it’s happening next summer or the summer after.

2. Who are you BEING during this vision? How do you act? Spend your time? What do you wear? How do you hold yourself? How do you move through life?

3. How are you acting now? How is it different than the version of you you saw in your vision?

4. What behaviors and patterns are not a match for the summer you want to create? 

5. What elements of your dream summer can you bring into the next 3-4 weeks?

Now - if you are done with just unconsciously going through life and want to make a statement and create the summer of your dreams now, you need to decide to become the version of you who has the ideal summer, BEFORE you have that external reality. You actually don’t need anything to be that person. 

🔥 Burn the list of patterns & behaviors you are leaving behind (the Full Moon is the perfect time to release things).

📖 Take your list of who are you BEING in your ideal summer and at the top write “I choose NOW to be” and read out your list out loud, like you mean it! The trees can be your witness.

Over the coming days, practice being this next version of you, and start creating little moments that are in your vision. You will be amazed that if you change who you are being, creating your external reality is so much easier.

The number one reason couples get divorced not only surprised me, but had me see why 50% of couples are choosing to end their relationships… 

The reason is 👉🏼 Career Choices 

Let’s break this down.

Here’s what often happens if you’re in a heterosexual couple. 

Scenario 1:

The man feels pressure to make a ton of money, and works his way up in a job he hates.  He comes home grumpy, isn’t as helpful around the house because he’s so drained. The the woman gets mad that he isn’t a more present parent, doesn’t help out and wants him to quit his job, which makes him feel stuck and unappreciated.

Then in this day in age, the woman wants to create a career based on her soul’s mission, and either isn’t given the space to invest and grow her company (so her male partner doesn’t understand why she’s not making money) or the woman is so bogged down in taking care of her kids and the house (because the husband is working so much) that she can’t get the business off the ground.

And then the couple isn’t on the same team, their dreams seem at odds, and neither of them feel supported, creating a rift they can’t come back from.

Scenario 2:

The woman has a successful career and can support the family, while the husband is barely contributing financially— which wouldn’t be a big deal if she wasn’t also doing 75% of the childcare & house work. The husband is not motivated, resentful, wishes he could make more money but feels so disempowered (and unwilling to do inner work) that he stays stuck. This couples often gets into a parent / child dynamic where the women feels like a mature adult and her husband feels like another kid.

RITUAL 👇🏼

Step 1: Create Sacred Space
I believe that we all remember how to create sacred space. If this is the first time doing it, you will be amazed at how comfortable and easy it feels once you get started. 

First create an altar. Lay a scarf or blanket down and create a circle of pillows. In the center, you can literally place anything. A few ideas: collect things from nature, seasonal food or flowers, or something to represent each element – water, fire, air, and earth. Put a candle at the center. Then grab a pot, some paper, a pen and matches.

Open the space by lighting a candle and asking everyone to close their eyes and breathe deeply. Then, share a prayer or an invocation, something like:

“Goddess, we are here to celebrate the amazing summer we had, and to welcome in fall. Please surround and protect the sacred circle, and please allow us each to speak our truth and call in everything we need to reach the fullest expression of who we are in this next season of our lives.”

But you can literally say whatever you want.

Step 2: Digest & Release the Summer 
Have everyone go around and say their favorite part of summer, then have everyone write down something they don’t want to take into Fall.

You will be amazed by the deep things that come out of our kids’ mouths sometimes!

Write down everything you are leaving in summer on a piece of paper & burn it in a pot.

Step 3: Fears & Intentions for the Fall
Now ask everyone to share what they are afraid or nervous about  this Fall. No need to respond or fix, just listen and say, “we hear you.”

Next, go around the circle & share what they want to feel this Fall, or one thing they want to accomplish. Write down each thing.

After everyone goes, close your eyes and take a few deep breaths together & ask everyone to imagine themselves in December, having accomplished all these things or feeling this way.

Then affirm with “And so it is.”

To complete you can move the altar to a plate on the kitchen counter or on a shelf somewhere and leave this list on the altar. Every once in a while, check in with this list.

Let’s make the change of season sacred again.

You’re growing, expanding, awakening. 

But are you and your partner BOTH committed to personal growth?

Maybe that looks different for each of you, but you’re both thinking about how to be the most alive, healthy, relaxed, successful, loving version of yourself. You meet every day as if it’s your last, you care about how you’re showing up as a parent, and you aren’t aimlessly going through life acting like it’s someone else’s job to make you happy.

Does each of you have a sense of self responsibility? Do you trust your partner to take care of themselves and show up for what they say they’re going to do without you needing to remind them?

➡️ If you said no to this question then you can relate to the majority of women I know. 

There’s been an incredible emphasis on women doing personal development work over the past 10 years. I have felt very lucky to be a teacher within the space. But there’s one thing that I’ve noticed if she’s married to a man who refuses to work on himself. And it’s that she can only go so far in her growth until she either feels so distant from her partner that she consciously holds herself back or she feels that her only option is to leave her marriage if she truly wants to be free to be herself.

You’re not the same as you were when you got married. Is your marriage a match for who you are now? 

I believe that working on ourselves is an important part of our generation. If you are dedicated to your personal growth, you have to be married to someone who’s just as committed to their personal growth as you are. @jonathanbrajtbord’s personal growth looks different from mine, but he’s done his own work and now we share a language, we’re interested in more similar things, and I don’t feel like a 38-year-old married to a 23-year-old. Believe me, I did feel that way for a long time and it was not great for our sex life. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

If you’re looking for support in making your marriage a match for who you are now — I think you’ll love Modern Marriage and our Sacred Union package that includes Holy Woman and Men’s Work.

Now, of course — communication in marriage is important. Critical even. But after working with hundreds of couples through our Modern Marriage program, @jonathanbrajtbord and I have seen even the most incredible communicators get stuck in the loop of conflict and exhaustion when there are years of unspoken agreements that have cause built up resentment, and have gone largely unchecked.

So then what’s the best marriage advice? In our opinion, it all comes down to this one magic word…

✨AGREEMENTS✨ 

Clear, co-created, and mutually upheld agreements about EVERYTHING in your marriage.

Couples who have shared agreements around…

✔️The vision they hold for their family life
✔️How the logistics of daily life flow
✔️Who’s responsible for each of the household duties like taking out the trash or getting the laundry put away
✔️Who the primary parent is in any given timeframe (down to who gets the kids shoes on in the morning)
✔️How the finances are managed and how financial decisions are made
✔️Showing up as their best self for each other (as opposed to giving it all away at work)
✔️How the romantic relationship is prioritized (when date nights happen, who is responsible for planning them, and what the goal of this romantic connection is)
✔️And our personal secret weapon —  How each partner is responsible for and prioritizes their own growth & inner work — and how the marriage can support that with the investment of time, space, energy, and money.

… are so much closer to an equitable, magnetic and joyful marriage than couples who are just great at talking it out.
