FALL EQUINOX 👇🏼

Mother Earth has an intelligence, and every physical shift and change is a message on how to be in the flow, to embrace our natural power and be more alive.

Fall starts with the harvest, a time when farmers pull food from the ground, harvest the wheat and the corn and get busy prepping and storing it for the winter. The animals are following suit gathering acorns and building winter proof homes. It’s a time of great activity, business, and organization. 

We’ve been in the sign of Virgo for almost a month now which carries that same energy of busyness and organization. 

Saturday is the Fall Equinox, the day that measures equal hours of light and dark; night and day are the same length – and it’s an invitation to think about balance. It is also when we move into the sign of Libra, whose symbol is the scales – again, balance. Traditionally in the Northern Hemisphere, it is a time to have a great Harvest Festival (which is what I’m doing this weekend!), to really celebrate all of the hard work of the year and rest after a month of the hard work of harvesting.

I define magic as aligning with the natural power of what’s happening around us. The Goddess/God/Divine (doesn’t matter what you call it) has created a world that moves in a certain pattern (Spring, Summer, Fall, Winter) which also corresponds with the moon phases (Waxing, Full Moon, Waning, New Moon), which also corresponds with our menstrual cycle (Follicular, Ovulation, Luteal, Bleeding). This rhythm of Grow, Harvest, Release, Rest is all around us. We can’t stop it, we can only ignore it.

In my own life and in Holy Woman, we align our personal growth with the seasons and the Moon. We use the natural rhythm to get information about what would serve our growth.

Here are a few prompts to help you tap into this energy:

What are you grateful for?
What are you releasing to bring things into balance?
What intention are you setting for the season ahead?

SACRED HAIRCUT RITUAL 💇‍♀️⁣

However, when we are deep in the systems of internalized patriarchy we believe that we can’t truly be ourselves in our relationships and instead become the people-pleaser and the peacemaker - sound familiar?

Are you hiding your magic?

If you…

•Hide your altar under your bed because you’re afraid of being judged 
•Keep your tarot cards in your underwear drawer because it’s just *too weird* 
•Have one foot in and one foot out on your spiritual practice 
•Can’t fully show up as your truest self in front of your spouse, family, or friends

I want to share that for the longest time, I was THAT person. I felt like two completely separate people, leading two 
separate lives. I was hiding my magic and not truly living out
When we wake up to our own magic, it can be jarring. It can feel so intense and so deeply profound, that we immediately feel the instinct to hide and bury it deep within so that we can’t be judged or harmed for it. 

We might even think —

“No one would “get it” anyway.”

“I could never explain what I’m actually doing to my parents.”

“It’s probably all just coincidence anyway.”

“I can just keep this part of me separate from everyone else. No one really needs to know this part of me.”

That is patriarchal conditioning at work, my love. 

They knew that if just one woman began to show her magic, then it would cause other women to finally start waking up to their own magic, too. This is the spark that lights the bonfire. This is why we can hide no longer. 

Think about the first woman you opened up to about your magic. Maybe it was about a sign from your guides, or a manifestation practice that worked, or a download you got during meditation, or an experience you had doing energy work, or something you saw in Ceremony. 

What did you see in her that made you feel safe to share it?

You are not different than she is. 

She is the spark, and you are the spark. 

If you’re ready to come out of the broom closet, to quit hiding your magic and to live a life that is fully expressed, sacred, magical, and juicy as hell — drop a 🔥 in the comments so we can celebrate your arrival.

3 simple ways to make your Thanksgiving more Sacred.

✨ Understand the true history of Thanksgiving
✨ Remember the symbolism of the foods on the table
✨ Ask meaningful questions around the table

So much of Thanksgiving - its true history and symbols - have gotten lost or erased over time, that by simply remembering, you are bringing an element of Sacredness to your Thanksgiving table.

The Harvest Meal was a Fall Equinox tradition dating back to the pre-Christian Europeans who honored Mother Earth’s bounty in the fall. SO thanksgiving is actually a Sacred Feminine tradition. 

How amazing is that?!

In our home, we use Thanksgiving as a time to educate our kids on the real history of Native Americans (which my kids still do not get in school) and celebrate their culture and their massive contribution to science, the arts, and environmental protection. 

Since my ancestors came over on the Mayflower, we also take the opportunity to talk about religious freedom, taking risks, and creating new legacies. And, we are clear with our kids that our ancestors were most likely involved in the genocide of the Native Americans, which is why it is really important for us to support our local native American tribes, and honor the original ancestors of the land we live on.

We also take the time to remember the ancient and sacred symbolism of the foods present around the table. Pecans, Oysters, and Turkey are all about fertility, while pumpkins and squash represent the womb. Cranberries can symbolize the bitterness of life and potatoes can help keep us grounded! 

Later this week, I’ll be sharing my go-to questions to ask around the Thanksgiving table…the ones that really help us and our loved ones go a layer deeper than the standard “I’m thankful for…” business. 

How do you plan on making your Thanksgiving more Sacred?

If you’ve always wanted the conversations around your Thanksgiving table to be more meaningful than the standard issue “This year I’m thankful for…,” this is your sign to take the lead. 

Be the sacred center of your family and bring the magic.

Swipe for 5 of my favorite questions to ask around the Thanksgiving table. Also, can we also answer #4 below? It’s my favorite! 

You’ll likely be shocked and delighted by the answers that come out of everyone’s mouths. Embrace the opportunity to be vulnerable and share authentically. 

This is how we go deeper. 

It starts right at our very own tables.

Happy Thanksgiving, loves!

December is the time for dreaming…and I’m not just talking about at night. In the darkest of days of the year, that’s only fitting, right? 

December is actually an incredibly powerful portal for manifestation. 

So, this month can you get quiet and sit with an inner stillness that reveals what your soul is actually craving? 

Can you take the opportunity to start holding and seeding the vision for the year to come?

We have an amazing astrology oracle dropping in Holy Woman in a few short days with @tamibrunk. So, be on the look out for even more ways the cosmos can support you this month!

HERE IT IS…⬇️

I know you want to have a Sacred Holiday season. And the truth is that it can just feel hard to make it happen.

Because there are a gazillion things to do, and everyone seems to have it more together than you do. 

But here’s what I want to share today.

It’s really ok to just sit down and have a cup of tea. 

The big “secret” to having a life that feels deeply Sacred (and to making this busy/magical season feel that way too) is to make everything a Living Ceremony.

Here’s what I mean:

- Stop what you are doing right now.
- Put the kettle on.
- Light a candle. 
- Turn on peaceful piano Christmas music.
- Take full, deep breaths while you wait for the water to boil. 
- Gaze at the flame of your candle while you breathe.
- Every time you inhale, let your breath fill your belly (a little more each time).
- Breathe in quiet nourishment.
- When you exhale, release your list of things to do. Release your overwhelm. 
- When your kettle begins to sing, move your awareness to what you’re calling in this season.
- As you brew your tea, add wishes and intentions for whatever is on your heart.
- Add a little honey, and think about something extra sweet you want to bring into your life.
- Bring your mug and your candle to a cozy spot, ideally where you can look out of your window (or even better, go outside).
- As you sip your tea offer gratitude to the Goddess (or God, or your angels, or yourself) for the beauty of your life. Get as specific as you can.
- With each sip, let the stillness of this moment move like honey through your body. Let the wishes and intentions that you put into your tea land in you.
- When you are complete, put your hand on your heart to honor this time and space.

It gets to be this simple, and this beautiful.

If you’re looking for more ideas like this one to make the holiday season Sacred again, just DM me the word HOLIDAY and I’ll send you my free Sacred Holiday Collection, complete with of Sacred Feminine workshops, rituals, lessons and guidance on bringing meaning and magic to this season.

This Collection was years in the making, and has the highest value of anything we’ve ever given away for free. I hope you love it.

For many of us who grew up going to church, the church was the source of the Sacred. In your life overall, but especially during the Holiday season.

And for those of us that grew up and realized that the church wasn’t in alignment for us and stopped going – we’re aching for a new source for the Sacred in our life. A new anchor. But most of us aren’t sure where to find it.

Maybe we try yoga. Meditation. Women’s circles.

It helps – it’s aligned, it’s good for us in so many ways.

But the Sacred void and the lack of a Sacred community gathering around prominent seasonal holidays is often still there.

In this community, what we’re offering is a new source for the Sacred. 

In Holy Woman, our Sacred Feminine Spiritual Community, we gather every moon cycle and honor the Wheel of the Year through Ceremony. We share the Sacred Feminine wisdom and stories that have been intentionally left out of the church’s teaching to push a patriarchal agenda. And we support each other in living from our Soul’s instead of from our conditioning. 

You get to reclaim the holiday season (and your whole life for that matter) as Sacred – for yourself and your family. In whatever way is in alignment for you. 

And if you’re looking for a Sacred community to land in, we would be honored to welcome you to Holy Woman. 

On 12/12 we are gathering in-person (spots are full) and on our global livestream for our HOLY NIGHT Winter Solstice Ceremony & Celebration. I finally gave up on being an organized Mom…who’s ready to throw in the towel with me? 

I will probably be wrapping presents on Christmas Eve again. My kids will likely cry on Christmas morning because they didn’t get the toy they wanted because I didn’t order it in time.

But instead of trying to be like everyone else, I’ve decided to play to my strengths, which for me are dance parties and rituals.

Today’s New Moon in Sagittarius encourages us to go where no woman has gone before and to be the seeker. Venus is in Scorpio which is asking all of us to cultivate our ALIVENESS. 

Put these together as we are set up to reach new levels of what it means for us to step all the way into our life force.

What edges come up for you when you think about allowing yourself to feel truly alive? How can you lean in anyways?

What do you need to shift in your attitude and in your small daily actions to create more life force?

Let’s make the Holidays Sacred (and fun!) again.

Happy New Moon.

Read this if you’re longing to make your Holidays feel Sacred again…

I know everything may feel chaotic right now, like there are a million things to do, people to see, things to buy, and events to plan for (uhm…because there are)…but can you stop and consider allowing the chaos feel wild, juicy, and sacred?

Can you allow the chaos to fuel a sense of aliveness and playfulness within you?

What would it feel like to take your cues from nature…from the bare trees, dormant grass, and setting sun? What would it look like to slow down, go inward, and start seeding dreams for a new season?

Can you bring your full presence into your vision for how you want to show up?

Here is your friendly reminder from the universe that presence and play can go a long way in making this time of year feel Sacred.

It doesn’t have to be complicated or fancy or over-the-top. Magic can be added to anything with a little bit of intention.

Show up. 
Go all in. 
Get still. 
Play full out.

If you’re wanting the Holidays to feel Sacred just comment HOLIDAY and I’ll send you my Sacred Holiday Collection, complete with of Sacred Feminine workshops, rituals, lessons and guidance on bringing meaning and magic to this season.

In our last New Moon Ceremony, a powerful visualization of Mother Mary (a high Priestess) pregnant came through in our Soul Journey meditation. 

While there are so many different facets of Mary’s story, the story of Mary birthing Jesus during this time of year is a powerful reminder of the divine potential within each of us.

As women, we are often taught to play small, to hold ourselves back, and to believe that our gifts are not worthy of sharing. But the truth is, we are all here for a reason. 

We each have a unique purpose and responsibility in this lifetime and it’s up to us to show up in our most authentic power. 

And in Sacred space, being in your authentic power means being in the truest, most full expression of who you really are regardless of what’s happening outside of you. I believe that this power is cultivated through our connection with the divine and through our life force that we create from within.

Owning our power can be scary and overwhelming, especially when we face the patriarchal norms that tell us we don’t belong, that we’re too much, or somehow not enough.

But the truth is, we are more powerful than we realize — we just aren’t accessing it. When we step into our purpose, we make a significant contribution to this world, a contribution that only we can make.

So, let’s take a moment to celebrate our unique gifts and talents. What is your purpose? What makes your soul come alive? 

Share with us in the comments below and let us inspire each other to shine our lights even brighter (especially as we move towards the darkest days).

P.S. if you want more ways to bring the Sacred Feminine into the holiday season just comment HOLIDAY. I’ll send you my Sacred Holiday Collection, which includes a retelling of the Christmas Story that centers Mother Mary 🌹

I’m here to tell you, beloved, there is room for it all.

Whether you relate to God, Goddess, Spirit, or The Universe…it doesn’t matter. 

You (and your family) get to decide what traditions you will keep and celebrate. That is the beauty of this season! There is so much acceptance and freedom in this day and age that I feel we often take for granted. How amazing is it that we are finally safe to celebrate how we see fit - whether it’s by putting up a Christmas tree, lighting a Menorah, or making an offering to the land?

I come from a traditional Christian background, while my husband was raised Jewish. We felt it was so important to give our children access to the traditions of both of these religions. We also honor the Earth and recognize a lot of the overlap between Earth-based practices and their more religious counterparts. Needless to say, we go FULL OUT. 

We have consciously created a household where we make space for all of our beliefs and lineages, and we hold that they are not in competition, and one does not exclude the other. We have found that not only do our multiple faiths and belief systems coexist, but they actually amplify each other when we look for the similarities.

Our homes need to be a microcosm of the world we want to create. Our traditions shape who we become. Take some time today to think about the messages you want your kids to receive during this holiday time. How can your traditions communicate your values?

If you’re looking for some specific guidance around how to weave the Sacred Feminine into your holiday traditions, comment HOLIDAY and I will send you my free Sacred Holiday Collection of rituals, workshops, guides and lessons to bring magic and meaning to this Sacred season.

Kids won’t remember all the presents they receive…but they will remember how the holidays felt. 

So, instead of my kids remembering a version of their mother that’s stressed out, snappy, and more frenzied than festive…

I’m hoping my children will remember the version of their mother dancing with them at full volume in the kitchen while the Holiday treats are baked in the oven.

Making The Holidays feel Sacred for your kids doesn’t have to be over-the-top, super, complicated, or even expensive. Your energy and presence go such a long way in making things Sacred, but if you need a few activities and ideas here are some of my favorite…

✨Singing/Caroling - some of my favorite simple songs for children are available in The Sacred Holiday Collection alongside our popular “Teaching Kids About Magic Workshop.”
✨Making or Baking a Yule Log - This is perfect to bring out around the Winter Solstice! 
✨Crafting - Make ornaments out of pinecones or dry out oranges and forage for greens to make your very own garland! There are endless ideas from Pinterest for crafts to keep little ones busy, but my advice is to keep it simple. 
✨Being Outside - We always love to light a big Bonfire on the Winter Solstice, for example! Nature walks are also the perfect way to educate kids about the different symbols of the season.
✨Storytelling - Telling about the birth of Jesus, about Mary, or even incorporating family stories of holidays past is a great way to weave in a bit more Sacredness. 
✨Gift-giving / Offerings - Have your children collaborate on family gifts and make something together, participate in an act of generosity (ex: donating or getting gifts for other families and children in need in your community), or even have your children create offerings for the land you live on.

So, take a moment and pause.

What do you hope your kids remember about the holidays? 

What sights, sounds, and tastes do you hope they remember?

What memories or traditions do you hope they pull out and want to recreate with their own families? 

For more ways to make the Holidays magical and meaningful, just comment HOLIDAY and I’ll send you The Sacred Holiday Collection asap!

LIGHT. MIRACLES. NEW LIFE.

If you look across religions, traditions, and holidays…these are the three things each one has in common. 

How beautiful is that?

When we dive into the deeper meaning of our holidays and celebrate more than one, my experience is that each holiday is more powerful, not less. 

When we open ourselves up to celebrating what feels real and true - even if they may seem to contradict or compete - we allow for more light, more miracles, and more opportunities to bring new life into this world…through our ideas, dreams, and energy.

There is a reason the same stories, metaphors, and myths have a way of showing up over and over again across time, history, and space. Our soul communicates in words on a page, stars in the sky, and stories told by mouth. 

So, my love can we remember to…

Remind ourselves that we are Sovereign enough to hold light within us during even the darkest of times?

Allow ourselves to manifest and believe in big, juicy, undeniable miracles?

Seed new ideas for this next season of life in a way that feels potent and promising?

It’s all right here for us, beloveds. In the myths, the mysteries, the magic.

We are entering the potent portal of Winter Solstice. It’s the longest night of the year, and with it comes an energy of being in the dark.

It is a time to retreat, find moments of quiet reflection, and nourish our souls with peace.

This may feel counterintuitive given the last-minute holiday hustle and bustle that seems to set in about this time, but by honoring our need for rest and restoration, we replenish our inner reserves and prepare ourselves for the emergence of new growth. 

As a chronic over-doer, this medicine is especially important for me – and it’s why Yule (or Solstice) is one of my favorite holidays of the year.

Swipe 👉 for 7 ways you can honor and celebrate the Winter Solstice.

In our family, we always honor Yule by pulling the kids from school. We light a fire, spend time outside on the land, make soup, and have each child open a magical Earthly/nature-related gift from Jonathan and me. It just gets better every year.

For me, connecting with these ancient traditions ignited a part of me that knows how connected I am to the magic of the Universe. 

When I pause and honor Solstice as a doorway from one way of living my life to another, I feel incredible power knowing the Universe is supporting me in letting go and leaving behind what I no longer want in my life in the darkness. 

Tell me - how do you honor the Winter Solstice?

Also, if you’d like my free 13-page Winter Solstice Guide with more history, recipes, rituals, and tips for honoring the Winter Solstice, just comment HOLIDAY and I’ll send it to you asap!🕯️

We’re remembering…

While “Dark Christmas Aesthetic” may be trending on Pinterest, and Instagram, and showing up in closets everywhere, those of us who remember and celebrate Winter Solstice, know these signs and symbols are far from a trend. 

Yule is the original Christmas and it also marks the longest night of the year. 

It was and is a deeply Sacred time of year.

It’s the time of year when the universe invites us to pause, get still, and go inward. 

My ancestors celebrated Yule for thousands of years before the birth of Christ. 

So on this High Holy Day, ask yourself…

What wisdom can we obtain if we just get quiet enough to hear our soul-self speak?

What rest can we enjoy whenever we take a hard pause to still ourselves and nourish our bodies?

What accomplishments from the year can we more deeply celebrate after taking a moment of intentional reflection?

Happy Winter Solstice / Yule loves!

The Sun has been reborn and we are in the middle of a great awakening. 

First, how are we feeling today after yesterday’s Winter Solstice? Tell me in the comments below 👇

Now that we are through the darkest day of the year, the light will grow each and every day until the Summer Solstice. 

Right now we are in a very potent portal for manifestation. 

Astrologically, we are in a 70 year period where we are aligned with the center of the galaxy. This happens only once every 26,000 years - so the energy happening right now is powerful and direct. 

There has never been a better time to claim who you are or who you are becoming.

Today, make time to go outside, hold your deepest desires in your heart, and allow the sun to wash over you and amplify these desires. 

Let it be simple.

If you’re anything like our family, you’re gearing up for a weekend full of festivities. 

In the midst of the last minute to-do’s, traveling, baking, hosting, present wrapping, and more…these 5 things are perfect in grounding me back to the present moment.

Creating and embodying the energy I want to feel is absolutely essential. 

Something as simple as lighting a candle to create sacred space, meditating as I make a cup of tea, or starting my day with a dance party can do wonders to lift the spirit and make everything feel infinitely more Sacred.

If you honor the birth of Jesus at Christmas, do not forget about Mary, a powerful Priestess who stood in her highest power and stepped confidently into her destiny to be a part of a great lineage of people who came to ground love and light on the planet.⁣

Remember that tyrannical leaders painted her as a weak, meak, virginal bystander when it was her sovereignty, power and strength that makes the story of Christmas so rich.

May we all remember that Yeshua wasn’t the Christ meaning “Anointed One” until he was anointed by Mary Magdalene, a Priestess in the same lineage as her Mother in Law.

Yeshua AND Mary Magdalene together came to show that God exists within all of us and symbolize the heiros gamos (when the sacred masculine meets the sacred feminine) both within us and between people and we don’t need a church, money or fancy titles to commune with the Cosmos - just our bodies, love and presence.

Yeshua was a disrupter. He shook up the status quo and put himself and his family in a lot of danger. Mother Mary could have followed her motherly instincts and told him to fit in, to tone it down, but she was clear on her mission, to love and support this man and to trust in his life purpose, just as she had trusted in hers.

The stories we hear shape our views on life, love, motherhood and how we show up. Let’s all start to share the truth of this moment and this life.

Merry Christmas.

Wisdom passed to me by @priestesspresence. 
Art by the revolutionary @natalielennard.

Unpopular opinion: New year, new you…is a lie. 

I believe you don’t have to immediately start planning your new life for Jan. 1 because I believe that the person you are gearing up to become already lives within you. 

She is you and you are her.

Now is the time to rest, beloved.

This space between the Christmas Holidays and the New Year often feels disorienting. Once the gifts are unwrapped and all the company has gone home, there can be a sense of emptiness after a month full of frenetic and festive energy.

I mean, how many times have you heard co-workers, friends, or loved ones say, “I just don’t even know what to do with myself right now?” 

Maybe the thing is…we aren’t supposed to be doing anything.

Maybe we aren’t supposed to be grinding or filling up our to-do lists.

Maybe we’re meant to sink into, what my friend Kate Northrup calls, the fertile void and get really still. Maybe we’re supposed to really take hold of this opportunity to rest so that we can truly step into our fullest potential and be the person we already are, just fully expressed, during the new year.

How are you inviting and allowing rest during this season?

You don’t need permission to slow down and rest, beloved...but just in case it would help, consider this your permission slip. 

I’m writing one for you and one for myself.

For the longest time, I considered (and even celebrated) myself as a chronic over-doer. So, I know firsthand how tempting it can feel to rush right into the next season or project. 

I often need to remind myself to slow down and really prioritize resting. I need to light the candle, open my journal, make a cup of tea, and meditate as I watch the snow fall outside of my window. 

Resting should be simple, easy even - but if you’re a chronic over-doer like I was whose baseline is stress, resting can often feel deeply uncomfortable. 

It can feel uncomfortable to sit in the stillness and finally hear what you may have been avoiding, numbing, or distracting yourself from.

However, when I really listen to what my body and soul need to feel alive and well nourished...I know in my bones that it’s not more hustling or “doing.” 

What I need is often more stillness, more presence, and a lot more simplicity. 

Can you relate? 

What does your body, soul, and spirit need right now?

Have you ever had a gut feeling that maybe you were meant for more?

If you’ve been here for awhile, you may know that the path to traditional success was very clear and laid out for me. I grew up in New England, graduated with honors, went to the number one liberal arts college, and got a great marketing job in Manhattan out of college. 

I was ticking all the boxes, but something just didn’t feel right in my heart. So, I decided to leave the clear cut path that had been laid out and decided to follow my heart instead.

After that, I spent over a decade building a multi-7-figure health and coaching business. I helped thousands of women overcome their emotional eating. I was widely published and spoke on many big stages. And I created a life that was fine...

My life was fine. 

It was good. 

Many people would say it was GREAT from the outside looking in. I had a swanky apartment, two kids, a soon-to-be doctor husband, and a nanny to help while I ran my coaching biz. 

But something still wasn’t sitting right in gut. 

So, I started wondering what would more look like? 

What would it look like to take up waaaaay more space in my life?

What would it look like to center my Soul and my Soul’s Work, my joy, my adventure, my creativity?

What would it look like to leave behind “fine” and trade it in for “F*CKING AMAZING?!” 

What would it look like to just do the damn thing?

If you know in your gut that you’re meant for more, but you’re just not sure what is next for you...comment QUIZ below. 

I’ll send you the link to my totally free 13-question quiz to help you get clear on What’s Next For You.

My word for 2023 was Ripen. I wanted to be more like a juicy peach, hanging out, waiting for life to be attracted to me - and less like a squirrel running around burying acorns. 

It took me 6 months of making the same mistakes & decisions over and over until I got really sick of myself.

I finally sunk in around the Summer Solstice and all I can say is honing the frequency of Ripen is 🫠.

Remember that your intentions are the initiations you’re signing up for. The Goddess is going to create the best Mystery School for you to learn the lessons you need to become a master at what you want.

My word for this year is Artist. 

I am tuning all the way into the Muse, the Creatrix, Divine inspiration and letting it all pour through my vessel and into my art, which is currently writing a book & designing my new home. Dear Goddess, may the Mystery School be kind, fun & full of wonder 🤞🏼🙏🏼.

Do you have a word yet?? Tell me below.

PS: these photos are definitely not from those months 🤣, in fact, many of them were taken on the same day. But! They do represent the tone of my year. I am about to start my 3rd year with @workplaybranding and it been such a delicious, creative partnership. If this year is about being seen, expression and upleveling, you may want to consider working with them. If you DM @workplaybranding the word SARAH you will receive a $1500 video package when you sign up!

One thing I never miss doing is participating in my Sacred Planning Ritual. I’ve been doing some version of this since 2015 and every year, I find that it’s the perfect exercise to set my intentions and manifest goals for the coming year in a powerful way. 

Here’s the thing… no matter what you’re calling in for yourself in 2024 - you’re going to need to carve out that time and space to be intentional about it. 

You’re going to need a plan for how you will tend to your own thriving. And most importantly, you’re going to need to set aside some time to decide how you’re showing up as your highest self in the new year. 

Bring your markers and your magic...here are the 5 steps to my can’t miss end-of-the-year Sacred Planning Ritual:

✨ Set the scene - How do you want this upcoming year to feel? Set your scene accordingly. Bring in elements or put yourself in a setting that exudes the energy and elements you’re hoping to bring into the upcoming year.

✨ Celebrate your past year - So often, especially when you are an ambitious woman (which I know you are), we skip over the most important part of intention setting, celebrating! Can you identify your highlight from 2023? How did you grow? What did you learn?

✨ Identify the obstacles - This year likely won’t be any easier than years before, BUT you can be more prepared going in! What could get in the way of you accomplishing your goals in 2023? What has been a common thing that has tripped you up over and over in the past?

✨ Get it on the calendar - When we put our goals on the calendar and actually see the time and space it will take up in our real lives, it allows us time to evaluate. Are you taking on too much in any one season? What do you need to shuffle, negotiate, or cancel in order to make these new goals a reality?

Bonus points if you bring in your family and friends to do this ritual with you!

Comment below👇if you have a Sacred ritual you do at the end of each year or going into the New Year! Let me know if you plan to participate in a Sacred Planning Ritual of your own.

I can’t wait to be on this journey with you. It’s going to be an incredible year!

In our Sacred Holy Woman community, we’ve made it a practice to regularly ask our members to reflect on their lives and share their Sacred Brags. 

These brags can be about something as big as scaling Mt. Everest and as tiny as drinking your coffee while it’s actually hot (aka a feat that feels almost as impressive as scaling Mt. Everest when you have three children running around). 

What are you proud of about yourself? What beautiful and amazing things are happening in your life? 

This year, I created a crew. I love my one-on-one friendships, and there’s something so special about being a part of a group.

The women I’ve deepened with are people I don’t have to be special around, or hold, or be a persona. I get to be my messy, human, wild self. We celebrate the shit out of each other, and call each other out when we are out of line. 

It has taken great vulnerability, and the loss of control that comes with revealing your whole self. It took time, and I’m celebrating that this crew has landed in my life. 

As the year draws to a close...we are asking for your ultimate Sacred Brags from 2023! We want to celebrate you in all your sparkly, bejeweled, fully expressed glory! 

Drop them in the comments below ⬇️

What would it feel like to be celebrated as your most fully alive and effortlessly embodied soul self? 

How would you show up? 

What would you do differently?

I need you to know that you are absolutely capable of creating the life that you’ve envisioned for yourself, and already have everything you need to do it. Even if you have been led to believe otherwise.

The only way for the world you have imagined to become your reality is to be that person now, show up for your life like that today, and bring that frequency into everything you do, always.

Whether that means wearing the sequins and dancing on the furniture or making space for yourself and tuning into nature...it’s up to you.

No more hiding. 

In fact, you’re being called alllll the way in.

It’s time.

Comment TIME to register for the first New Moon Ceremony of the year on 1/11. It’s going to be extra juicy as we vision, plan, and manifest for 2024. Plus, it’s totally free to attend for anyone! Can’t wait to see you there, my loves

Swipe ➡️ for 5 journal prompts I use to help me at the beginning of each new year.⁣
Here’s the big “secret” to why claiming what you want matters: 

Your desires, the things that your Soul really wants – are breadcrumbs to your fullest expression and your highest service to humanity. If it’s in you, it’s for you – and it’s why no two people have the exact same dreams. 

Who is the person who has this dream life? How does she move through the day in a Sacred way? What frequency does she carry?

No one is coming with a big permission slip, with loads more time and more energy, or with a whole bunch of money to fund your big dreams. No one is coming. It’s just you.
And it’s time.

If you are longing for ritual & community, visioning & strategic support, ceremony & celebration…Join us for IT’S TIME, the first New Moon Ceremony of the New Year on 1/11. It’s totally free.

Raise your hand if you’ve ever been told or asked the following (or something similar) 🙋‍♀️

“When is it ever going to be enough for you?”
“You just want WAY too much.”
“You keep moving the benchmark.”

Yep, I’ve been there. I’ve heard this and experienced being on the receiving end of these comments more than my fair share. 

But let me tell you this, love:

You are NOT too much. 

What if you know what can be possible and what people are capable of?

What if you don’t want too much?

You are unconventional in the best way possible. You have a strong vision for the future and often it takes people like you - the trendsetters, trailblazers, and vision holders to go first. 

You help the collective rise to the occasion of imagining just how sacred, magical, and utterly exuberant their life could be! Deep in your soul, you know it’s up to you to create the life you were meant to have. 

If you’re ready to go first, to lead the way, and tap into the vision you have of your highest self…join us for IT’S TIME on 1/11. It’s the first New Moon Ceremony of the year and the perfect time to manifest and plan your more aligned and soul-nourishing 2024.

Comment TIME and I’ll DM you the details!

It’s so easy to wait around for someone else to give us permission to take the next step in our lives…maybe without even realizing it.

How many times have you wished that your mother, partner, boss, or friend would just sit down next to you and say, “You know what? You should really go after your dream! How can I support you?”

Guess what? It’s never going to happen exactly that way.

And you know why that is? It’s because…

YOU have to take the first step.
YOU have to give your permission.

“I want to live a more sacred and magical life, but where do I even start?”

I’ve been asked this question hundreds of times and so you can rest, assured that I’ve had a lot of practice answering it. Every single time, I come back to the 3 foundational things I think have helped me (and countless other women) live a more Sacred-Feminine-centered life.

So, if you want life to feel a bit more sacred here is where I recommend beginning: 

Daily Sacred Start - How we start our days, sets the tone. I’ve been carving out about an hour of Sacred Start time every single day for the past several years and it has transformed my life in the best way. When I prioritize time for myself to meditate, journal, pull cards, sip tea, or do anything else I need to - I’m a better wife, mother, and person for it.

Sacred Feminine Ceremony Each Moon Cycle - I have yet to find anything as powerful and transformative as Sacred Feminine Ceremony. If you’ve never been in a Sacred Feminine Ceremony, I highly recommend it. Women have gathered together in circles for thousands of years and there is something so energetically potent about it that you have to experience first-hand. That’s why we gather on every New Moon in Holy Woman.

A Sacred In-Person Pilgrimage - This one is new, but one thing that I’ve found is SO important. There is something powerful about finding a Sacred spot or location in the universe and returning to it time after time. We all have those Sacred places...those places that make us feel something. The places that draw us in over and over again, even if only in our dreams. 

Each Fall Equinox hundreds of women make the Pilgrimage to Hawthorn Farm and sit in ceremony and celebration for 3 full days. It is easily one of my favorite and most sacred weekends of the year. We honor the land with offerings, we sing, dance, meditate, and come alive together.

If you feel called to or drawn to Emerge Retreat / Hawthorn Farm, be sure to snag your spot now (I know the fall seems far away, but I promise it will come quicker than you can imagine!). We have limited spots and presale pricing ends 1/23/24.
